The paper discusses resource allocation for mobile edge computing in the context of Augmented Reality (AR) applications on mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with communication networks and protocols. The paper also involves multimedia processing and computer vision, which suggests categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses energy consumption, which could fall under categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
